  "texts": [
    "LiabilityRegarding the use of AI in medicine, it is imperative to address the concept of liability in the informed consent process.",
    "Patients should be clearly informed of the potential for errors and liability issues associated with AI-driven medical decisions [52].",
    "This conversation should entail a discussion on who bears responsibility, including the liability of physicians, if an AI system malfunctions or leads to incorrect medical outcomes such as misdiagnoses or inappropriate treatment plans.",
    "The explicit clarification of liability, particularly the role and responsibility of health care providers in conjunction with AI, is important for helping patients understand the potential risks involved [53].",
    "This understanding is a key component of a comprehensive informed consent process that directly affects the patients' trust in AI and their treating physicians."
  ],
